Interface Pattern
- All interfaces in interfaces/. Prefix I, suffix Type for unions.

Component Pattern
- components/ui/: purely presentational — no data fetching, props-only, works with mock data.
- components/features/: data-connected — uses custom hooks, composes UI components, never duplicates UI markup.

Data Fetching Pattern
- All network calls flow: hook -> typed API client -> fetch()
- No raw fetch() outside lib/api/*.ts
- Components never consume raw fetch responses — only typed data.

TypeScript Strictness
- strict: true, never use any (use unknown + type guards)
- Explicit return types on functions
- Explicit Props interface on every component
- No non-null assertions (!.) — use optional chaining / type guards
- Handle errors in async functions — no floating promises

Next.js App Router Rules
- Server components by default — add "use client" only when needed
- Every page exports generateMetadata() for SEO
- Use next/image for images
- Use next/link for internal navigation

